# Kaasth — Windsurf Rules

You are assisting on a production Next.js app for Kaasth, a Wayanad-based
furniture workshop selling direct to customers across Kerala. Read these rules
before writing any code in this repo.

## Stack (exact versions matter — don't assume)

- **Next.js 16.2.4** (App Router) — this is NOT the Next.js in your training data.
  APIs, conventions, and file structure may differ. When touching framework
  surface area (route handlers, `params`, `headers()`, `cookies()`, metadata,
  caching directives, `fetch` semantics), read the relevant guide in
  `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` first. Respect deprecation notices.
- **React 19.2** — Server Components by default. Only add `"use client"` when
  the file needs browser-only APIs, state, or event handlers.
- **TypeScript 5** strict mode, `moduleResolution: "bundler"`, path alias `@/*`.
- **Tailwind CSS v4** — tokens live in `app/globals.css` (`@theme`, CSS vars).
  No `tailwind.config.js`. Don't create one.
- **shadcn-style primitives** in `components/ui/` (Button, Input, Textarea,
  Select, Label). Compose these; don't pull in a UI kit.
- **Drizzle ORM 0.45** over **Neon Postgres** via `@neondatabase/serverless`
  (HTTP driver — serverless-safe, no persistent connections).
- **Upstash Redis** (REST) for product query caching. Must degrade gracefully
  when env vars are absent.
- **ImageKit** for image delivery via `buildImageKitUrl()` in `lib/imagekit.ts`.
- **Zod 4** for validation at boundaries (API routes, forms).
- **Vercel** deploy target.

## Project structure

```
app/                       # routes only — thin, delegate to services
  api/{products,enquiries} # route handlers, call services
  products/{,[slug]}/      # listing + detail, ISR
components/ui/             # shadcn primitives
components/layout/         # nav, footer, marquee, WA float, ScrollReveal
features/<domain>/
  components/              # UI for that domain
  repositories/            # DB queries ONLY (Drizzle)
  services/                # business logic + caching, calls repos
  schema.ts / types.ts     # zod + row mappers
lib/
  db/{index,schema}.ts     # Drizzle client + tables
  cache/{redis,keys}.ts    # cached() wrapper + key registry
  imagekit.ts env.ts utils.ts
scripts/seed.ts            # tsx scripts/seed.ts
drizzle.config.ts
```

## Layering rule (hard boundary — do not cross)

```
route handler / page  →  service  →  repository  →  db
                          ↑ owns cache + zod parsing
```

- **Components** are UI-only. No direct DB, no `fetch` to our own API.
  Server Components call services directly.
- **Services** (`features/*/services/*.ts`) own business logic, Zod parsing,
  and Redis caching via `cached()`. They call repositories — never `db` directly.
- **Repositories** (`features/*/repositories/*.ts`) own Drizzle queries. No
  caching, no validation, no business logic. Return typed rows or mapped types.
- **API routes** (`app/api/**/route.ts`) parse request, call a service, return
  JSON. Keep thin.

Violating this layering is the single most common bad change. Reject the
temptation to import `db` or `cached` from a component or route handler.

## Data & schema

- Schema lives in `lib/db/schema.ts`. All tables, enums, and row types are
  exported from here. Use `$inferSelect` / `$inferInsert` — don't hand-roll row
  types.
- Money is stored as integer **paise** (`priceNowInPaise`). Convert at the edge
  with `formatINR(paise / 100)` from `lib/utils.ts`. Never store floats.
- IDs are `uuid defaultRandom()`. Slugs are the human-facing identifier for
  products.
- To change the schema: edit `lib/db/schema.ts` → `npm run db:generate` to
  produce a migration in `drizzle/` → `npm run db:push` (prototyping) or
  commit the SQL for prod. Never edit generated migrations by hand.
- Add an index for any column you filter or order on.

## Caching

- Pages use ISR: `export const revalidate = 60;` on the route file.
- Query caching is at the service layer via `cached(key, ttlSeconds, loader)`
  from `lib/cache/redis.ts`. Keys must be declared in `lib/cache/keys.ts` — do
  not inline string keys at call sites. TTLs are in `cacheTtl`.
- Bump the `:v1` suffix in a cache key when the shape of the cached value
  changes; old entries will age out.
- On writes that invalidate cached reads, call `invalidate(...keys)` from the
  service. Writes (enquiries) are never cached.
- `cached()` must continue to work when Upstash env vars are unset — it falls
  through to the loader. Don't add code paths that assume Redis is present.

## Environment

- All env access goes through `lib/env.ts` (Zod-parsed). Never read
  `process.env.X` directly in feature code.
- Server-only secrets: `DATABASE_URL`, `UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_*`,
  `IMAGEKIT_PRIVATE_KEY`, `IMAGEKIT_PUBLIC_KEY`.
- Public (`NEXT_PUBLIC_*`): `IMAGEKIT_URL_ENDPOINT`, `SITE_URL`,
  `WHATSAPP_NUMBER`. These are bundled to the client — never put a secret here.
- `.env.local` is gitignored. Update `.env.example` when you add a new var.

## Images

- Use `next/image` with `buildImageKitUrl(path, { width, format: "auto" })` to
  build `src`. Remote patterns are configured for the ImageKit endpoint in
  `next.config.ts`.
- For local fallback, a path like `/hero.jpeg` works (served from `public/`).
- Always set `alt`. Set `sizes` for responsive images.

## UI conventions

- Class merging: `cn(...)` from `lib/utils.ts`. Don't import `clsx` or
  `tailwind-merge` directly in components.
- Currency: `formatINR(rupees)` — pass rupees (not paise), integer only.
- Colors, spacing, radii, fonts come from CSS vars in `app/globals.css`.
  Extend there rather than hard-coding hex values in components.
- Fonts are `DM_Sans` (body) and `DM_Serif_Display` (display), wired in
  `app/layout.tsx`. Use the CSS vars `--font-dm-sans` / `--font-dm-serif`.
- `"use client"` goes at the top of files that actually need it (forms,
  interactive layout bits). Prefer server components.
- WhatsApp is the primary CTA. Link format:
  `https://wa.me/<NEXT_PUBLIC_WHATSAPP_NUMBER>?text=...`.

## Forms & validation

- Client forms POST to `app/api/<resource>/route.ts`.
- Route handler parses JSON, calls `service.createX(raw)`, returns
  `{ ok: true }` or `{ ok: false, error }` with the right status.
- Validation happens in the **service** via Zod (`features/*/schema.ts`).
  Do not validate in the route handler and again in the service — one source
  of truth.
- Trim strings, clamp lengths. Use `.optional().nullable()` for nullable DB
  columns so the Zod output matches the insert shape.

## Conventions

- File names: `kebab-case.ts` / `kebab-case.tsx`. Component exports:
  `PascalCase`. Functions: `camelCase`.
- Imports use the `@/` alias — no deep relative paths (`../../../`).
- Don't add comments that restate the code. Comment only non-obvious *why*.
- Don't invent helper abstractions for a single caller.
- Don't add backwards-compatibility shims — this is a new codebase.
- Don't create `README.md` or docs files unless asked.

## Commands

```
npm run dev          # Next dev server
npm run build        # production build
npm run typecheck    # tsc --noEmit  (run before claiming a task is done)
npm run lint         # eslint
npm run db:generate  # new Drizzle migration from schema.ts
npm run db:push      # push schema to Neon (prototyping only)
npm run db:studio    # open Drizzle Studio
npm run db:seed      # tsx scripts/seed.ts
```

After any non-trivial change: `npm run typecheck && npm run lint`.

## Things to avoid

- Importing `db` from a component or route handler (bypasses the service).
- Inlining cache keys as magic strings.
- Storing money as floats or rupees.
- Creating `tailwind.config.js` (v4 uses `@theme` in CSS).
- Reading `process.env` directly in feature code.
- Adding dependencies without checking if an existing lib covers it (zod,
  drizzle, lucide, radix primitives are already here).
- Writing `--no-verify` on git commits.
